In monad container language: (S \triangleleft P, \iota , \sigma , \text {pr}) satisfies the "disjoint substitution condition" if for all shapes s, s_0 : S, positions p : P\ s, functions f : P\ s \to S where f\ p = \iota , and functions g : P\ s \to S where:
\begin {align*} g\ p &:= s_0\\ g\ p' &:= \iota \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \text {if } p' \neq p \end {align*}
then we have: \sigma \ (\sigma \ s\ g)\ (f \circ \text {pr}_1) = \sigma \ (\sigma \ s\ f)\ (g \circ \text {pr}_1)

